        dc:description           "FIG. 12. — Mandible and postcranial remains of Chilcacetus cavirhinus n. gen., n. sp., MUSM 1401: A, B, fragment of right dentary in lateral (A) and dorsal (B) views; C-F, vertebrae (corresponding to vertebrae 1-3 in Table 2); C,?cervical in anterior or posterior views; D, cervical or thoracic in anterior or posterior views; E, F, thoracic in anterior or posterior views (E) and dorsal view (F); G, H, rib fragments. Note the shark tooth marks in H (arrows). Scale bars: A, B, 50 mm; C-F, G, H, 20 mm." ;
